just_use peel_for_run.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Hand card V finds board cards at V-1 and V+1 that can both be extracted,
such that the three cards form a valid 3-run (pure or rb). The two board
cards get peeled from different stacks (same-stack rejected) and the new
run is pushed.

**Apply ordering matters.** extractCard changes indices; we extract the
higher (stackIdx, cardIdx) first so the earlier index stays valid, then
re-locate the second target on the intermediate board. relocate re-finds
by card identity, not positional reuse.
